You are informed that you will be the next therapist authorized to use the D.I.V.E. Unit.

"Before we begin," said Doctor Hammond.
"there are only two things you need to remember."

"First, do not remain inside a dream for too long. Extended exposure blurs your sense of reality," he continued.

"Second, observe before you act. Reckless decisions inside a patient’s mind can alter your own personality." He finished the explanation taking the device from what it seemed to be a drawer, positioning it on a table in front of you.

"This, is the D.I.V.E Unit"

The procedure can be stopped.
The consequences cannot.



