:: StudyPieces {"position":"1100,1500","size":"100,100"}
You crouch slightly, examining the pieces’ movements.

Slowly, patterns emerge. The precise, unyielding motions of pawns and knights reveal Theodore’s strictness as a teacher, every action measured, every mistake punished by the shifting formation of the other pieces.

The dream feels rigid, unforgiving, yet fascinatingly precise.


